cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SP. 

The paper discusses optimizing sensing matrices for compressed sensing, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in arXiv CS. The focus on optimizing matrices for the CACTI camera suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a likely sub-category. The use of mutual coherence minimization and the investigation of the reliability of the coherence bound suggest cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely sub-category. The examination of bound looseness and the introduction of a new paradigm for optimizing sensing matrices suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) as additional likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of simulated data suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible sub-category as well.
